com.nokia.maps.routing

Interface RouteLeg


  • public interface RouteLeg
    This interface defines a route leg, which represents a section of a route between two consecutive waypoints.

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      double getLength()
      The method retrieves the length of the route leg.
      Maneuver[] getManuevers()
      This method retrieves a list of all maneuvers which are included in this section of the route.
      double getTravelTime()
      The method retrieves the time needed to travel the length of the given route leg.

    • Method Detail

      • getLength

        double getLength()
        The method retrieves the length of the route leg. It refers to one of the waypoints in the Route object, an element in Route.waypoints.
        Returns:
        the length of the route leg in metres

      • getManuevers

        Maneuver[] getManuevers()
        This method retrieves a list of all maneuvers which are included in this section of the route.
        Returns:
        a list of all maneuvers which are included in this section of the route.

      • getTravelTime

        double getTravelTime()
        The method retrieves the time needed to travel the length of the given route leg. The routing type determines if this value takes into account traffic information.
        Returns:
        The time needed to travel the length of the given route leg in seconds.
